00:17.059 --> 00:19.268
Ladies and gentlemen...

00:27.277 --> 00:29.195
We're in Moscow
in the Soviet Union,

00:29.279 --> 00:33.282
and this promises to be the most
watched event in boxing history.

00:42.793 --> 00:44.419
I must break you.

00:49.174 --> 00:50.216
Throw your right!

00:50.300 --> 00:52.385
He just will not let him
out of that corner.

00:52.469 --> 00:53.678
Rocky!

00:55.973 --> 00:58.474
Rocky Balboa is
in serious trouble.

00:58.559 --> 00:59.934
He's getting
killed out there.

01:03.105 --> 01:05.815
Drago continuing to
punish Rocky Balboa.

01:08.777 --> 01:11.404
No pain!
No pain.

01:13.407 --> 01:15.324
Rocky's been hit
with bombs.

01:15.576 --> 01:16.951
Rocky's hurt!

01:18.537 --> 01:23.040
Right hand from Drago sends Rocky
Balboa 15 feet across the ring.

01:23.125 --> 01:24.459
And his head's down.

01:25.502 --> 01:26.794
Come on, get up!

01:30.507 --> 01:32.633
It's been
a one-sided fight so far.

01:33.719 --> 01:37.430
And Drago throws a hard right
hand that stuns Rocky Balboa.

01:39.850 --> 01:43.269
They might have to stop this
one before somebody gets killed.

01:48.358 --> 01:51.694
Rocky taking punishment.
He is completely exhausted.

02:04.166 --> 02:07.043
And Balboa goes down again
from a right hand.

02:15.219 --> 02:16.594
Taking punch after punch.

02:16.678 --> 02:18.012
Amazing willpower.

02:22.559 --> 02:26.312
Rocky Balboa's taking Ivan
Drago's best punches so far.

02:26.396 --> 02:28.481
He's cut
and he's bleeding.

02:28.565 --> 02:30.191
All right,
what's happening out there?

02:30.275 --> 02:31.776
I see three of him
out there.

02:32.277 --> 02:34.111
Hit the one in the middle.
Right!

02:34.196 --> 02:35.279
Hit the one in the middle.

02:36.949 --> 02:37.990
The Russian's cut!

02:38.075 --> 02:39.283
Hit him!

02:44.706 --> 02:46.332
Whoa! Get him! Yeah!
Go!

02:54.591 --> 02:56.300
Hits the ground
like a wrestler.

02:56.385 --> 02:57.760
It's a gutter war!

02:57.845 --> 02:59.637
No holds barred in Moscow.

02:59.721 --> 03:03.182
All your strength, all your
power, everything you've got!

03:03.267 --> 03:04.517
Now, this is your
whole life here.

03:05.727 --> 03:08.187
And a big right hand
by Rocky Balboa!

03:13.193 --> 03:15.987
Rocky Balboa has
done the impossible!

03:17.281 --> 03:18.406
Yeah!

03:20.993 --> 03:25.705
Rocky! Rocky! Rocky!

03:39.887 --> 03:42.722
Man. I never saw nothing like it!

03:42.806 --> 03:44.807
Came through like
the champ you are.

03:45.559 --> 03:50.313
You did yourself and everybody
proud, especially Apollo.

03:50.397 --> 03:51.522
Yo, Tony.

03:51.607 --> 03:53.983
Yeah, what is it, baby?
What do you need?

03:54.067 --> 03:55.818
Get Adrian.

04:08.457 --> 04:09.498
Rocky?

04:09.833 --> 04:12.585
How's everybody
doing out there?

04:12.669 --> 04:15.421
Everybody...
Everything's okay.

04:16.839 --> 04:18.214
What's wrong?

04:20.636 --> 04:21.761
What's wrong?

04:21.845 --> 04:27.183
Remember when Mick said
when he was fighting,

04:27.267 --> 04:31.687
sometimes he'd fight so hard
that he was thinking that

04:32.147 --> 04:37.526
he broke something inside,
and he was gonna die,

04:37.611 --> 04:42.531
and that's what he said, that's
when the angels was pulling on him.

04:44.034 --> 04:46.202
Rocky, you're scaring me.
I don't know...

04:46.286 --> 04:47.328
What's wrong?

04:47.412 --> 04:49.622
Adrian, I can't...

04:49.706 --> 04:50.873
Can't what?

04:53.543 --> 04:55.586
I can't stop my
hands from shaking.

04:59.675 --> 05:01.300
I never felt this thing.

05:01.385 --> 05:02.677
You gotta see a doctor.

05:02.761 --> 05:04.261
No, I...
Right away. Yeah!

05:04.388 --> 05:06.430
No, I just wanna go home.
No.

05:06.515 --> 05:07.932
No.
You can see a doctor.

05:08.016 --> 05:09.308
I'm just tired.

05:11.895 --> 05:13.813
I just wanna go home, Mick.

05:13.897 --> 05:14.939
And I'm just tired.
I just...

05:15.023 --> 05:15.982
Okay.

05:16.066 --> 05:18.442
I just... I just wanna go home, okay?

05:18.527 --> 05:19.527
Okay.

05:21.780 --> 05:22.822
Okay.

05:41.758 --> 05:43.342
Adrian, where's the kid?

05:43.427 --> 05:44.927
I don't know.

05:45.512 --> 05:49.724
I don't see the kid. Where's
the kid? Ain't he here?

05:49.975 --> 05:51.767
Dad! Dad!

05:51.852 --> 05:53.352
There he is! There he is!

05:53.437 --> 05:55.896
Hey, slugger, how you doing?

05:55.981 --> 05:57.773
Say hi to your mom over there. Hi, Mom!

05:57.858 --> 05:58.899
Then I'm forgotten now?

05:58.984 --> 06:01.068
Hi, Uncle Paulie.
Dad, how you feeling?

06:01.153 --> 06:03.070
Well, I got a few new dents.
How you doing in school?

06:03.155 --> 06:05.114
I made the honor roll.
You're beautiful! Home team!

06:05.240 --> 06:06.782
Hi, I'm Sheila Downes,
airport security. Hi.

06:06.867 --> 06:08.159
Welcome home.
If you'll follow me

06:08.243 --> 06:09.410
there's a press
reception inside.

06:10.912 --> 06:13.956
Rocky, how did you feel about
the Russian people in general?

06:14.041 --> 06:16.125
You know, it was very
good. They was great people.

06:16.209 --> 06:19.045
I mean, I didn't understand what
they was speaking all the time,

06:19.129 --> 06:21.255
but I think I understood what
they was meaning, you know?

06:21.339 --> 06:23.299
Mrs. Balboa, did you learn any Russian?

06:23.633 --> 06:24.675
Did I learn...

06:24.760 --> 06:26.552
Yeah, yeah,
she got fluent in vodka.

06:26.636 --> 06:27.636
Hey, yo, Paulie...

06:27.721 --> 06:28.763
Paulie.

06:28.847 --> 06:32.058
Rocky, there are rumors of physical
complications after the fight.

06:32.142 --> 06:33.225
Complications?

06:33.310 --> 06:35.394
No, no,
those were rumors.

06:35.479 --> 06:38.439
He's in perfect
physical condition.

06:39.733 --> 06:41.192
Rocky. Rocky,
a question.

06:41.276 --> 06:44.070
Recently the American Medical
Association recommended

06:44.154 --> 06:45.446
that boxing be banned.

06:45.530 --> 06:46.530
Yeah?

06:46.615 --> 06:47.740
Do you agree
with the doctors?

06:47.824 --> 06:49.825
Yeah, you know, absolutely.

06:49.910 --> 06:51.827
I think that doctors
should never fight. No.

06:51.912 --> 06:54.455
That was a beautiful
answer, champ. That's right.

06:54.539 --> 06:56.290
Doctors should
stay out of the ring.

06:56.374 --> 06:57.750
Doctors should never fight.

06:57.834 --> 06:59.585
They should stay out
of the ring forever.

06:59.669 --> 07:02.254
Rocky Balboa,
the funniest champion ever.

07:02.339 --> 07:05.424
America's own Rocky Balboa.
How are ya? How are ya?

07:05.509 --> 07:07.051
George Washington Duke here,

07:07.135 --> 07:10.763
promoter extraordinaire,
welcoming back Rocky Balboa,

07:10.847 --> 07:13.682
champion of all the Americans
and all of the Russians.

07:13.767 --> 07:16.560
Now, I would like to digress
from the questions a bit

07:16.645 --> 07:19.355
and pose an interesting
proposition to the media.

07:19.439 --> 07:22.274
Everyone in this city,
certainly in the world of sports,

07:22.359 --> 07:24.235
knows my reputation
for promoting

07:24.319 --> 07:25.444
some of
the finest extravaganzas...

07:25.529 --> 07:26.612
I... What...

07:26.696 --> 07:28.197
...in this country.

07:28.281 --> 07:30.616
Well now,
with the press present,

07:30.700 --> 07:32.576
I'd like to ask you,
Rocky Balboa...

07:32.661 --> 07:33.661
Yeah?

07:33.745 --> 07:38.124
...to be the flamboyant, rambunctious
sportsman we know you can be,

07:38.208 --> 07:40.584
and give this man
here, Union Cane,

07:40.669 --> 07:44.296
a chance to challenge you for the
heavyweight championship of the world.

07:44.381 --> 07:47.299
Balboa, I want the opportunity
to take what you got.

07:48.468 --> 07:50.678
Isn't this bad timing to
present a challenger, Duke?

07:50.762 --> 07:52.263
The man just
got off the plane.

07:52.347 --> 07:55.599
Timing is the essence of
life, gentlemen and ladies.

07:55.684 --> 07:59.186
Now, what I have on this
paper is the largest guarantee

07:59.271 --> 08:02.398
ever offered to
a champion on this planet!

08:02.566 --> 08:06.318
I'm talking about a fantastic
international extravaganza,

08:06.403 --> 08:10.239
to be held in Japan, called
"Letting It Go in Tokyo. "

08:11.449 --> 08:13.450
People, ain't it incredible
that only in America

08:13.535 --> 08:15.369
could people like us
rise from oppression,

08:15.453 --> 08:19.707
rise from poverty, to join hands
in this international event?

08:19.791 --> 08:20.875
Only in America!

08:20.959 --> 08:22.042
Excuse me!

08:23.253 --> 08:26.338
Excuse me.
My husband is retired.

08:26.423 --> 08:29.008
He has nothing... He has
nothing more to prove.

08:29.092 --> 08:30.384
Hey, wait a minute!
Wait a minute!

08:30.468 --> 08:33.511
Hey, Rocky, don't you consider
this a public responsibility

08:33.597 --> 08:35.890
to respond now
rather than later?

08:36.265 --> 08:37.390
Respond to the people.

08:37.475 --> 08:39.602
I mean, isn't this a
question of professionalism?

08:39.686 --> 08:41.645
To talk about it now,
not later.

08:41.730 --> 08:43.188
Mind if I heal first?

08:43.273 --> 08:45.608
The whipping you got ain't nothing
like what I got here for you.

08:45.692 --> 08:47.067
So, what in the hell
does this all mean?

08:47.152 --> 08:50.154
No, that isn't enough.
We gotta hear about this now.

08:50.238 --> 08:52.114
Gotta think about that.
So, anyway,

08:52.199 --> 08:56.744
I wanna tell everybody that
the flight over was really nice.

08:57.579 --> 08:58.871
Come on, guys.
We need more!

08:58.955 --> 09:00.915
Adrian, you know,
if you weren't with me,

09:00.999 --> 09:02.583
I never would
have done as good.

09:02.667 --> 09:04.710
You're my Adrian... You're
always there, you know?

09:04.794 --> 09:09.256
And my kid, having you is
like being born all over again.

09:09.424 --> 09:12.259
Come on, what do you say?
Are you gonna retire or not?

09:12.344 --> 09:15.554
Anyway, I'd like... Excuse
me. I'd like to go home now.

09:15.639 --> 09:17.014
Are you gonna give us
something to write?

09:17.140 --> 09:19.058
Thank you very much. I
appreciate it. What do you say?

09:19.476 --> 09:20.559
No.

09:24.105 --> 09:28.067
Don't worry. You'll
get him. You'll get him.

09:48.588 --> 09:50.673
I know.
Really, it's great.

09:52.175 --> 09:55.135
Yo, look at this place.

09:56.054 --> 09:58.097
I swear, I ain't never
leaving this place again,

09:58.181 --> 09:59.181
you know that?

09:59.266 --> 10:02.601
I swear... Hey, would you like to dance?

10:02.686 --> 10:04.603
How about a homecoming
dance with your old man?

10:04.688 --> 10:06.105
No, don't be silly.
It's cold.

10:06.189 --> 10:08.107
Come on. I'll warm you up, young lady.

10:08.191 --> 10:10.776
Come on, have a dance. Hurry
up, the music's almost over.

10:12.988 --> 10:14.071
Do you like the song?

10:14.239 --> 10:15.531
You should rest.

10:15.615 --> 10:17.157
Yeah, I know.
I'm tired. Come on.

10:17.242 --> 10:18.784
Yeah? Well, maybe I'll take you upstairs

10:18.868 --> 10:20.953
and violate you
like a parking meter.

10:21.496 --> 10:22.788
It'll cost you
a quarter.

10:22.872 --> 10:24.331
Yo, Adrian!

10:24.416 --> 10:26.542
Where'd you learn to
talk dirty like that?

10:29.504 --> 10:33.173
Hey, Uncle Paulie, you notice
something strange about Dad?

10:33.717 --> 10:36.260
He just took
a few hard shots.

10:36.344 --> 10:39.596
I think you tell better
jokes than me, Adrian.

10:42.851 --> 10:45.894
Yo, did I hear somebody
call for their old man?

10:45.979 --> 10:47.313
Did you do this?

10:47.397 --> 10:49.565
Hey, it's sleep time,
kid, okay?

10:49.649 --> 10:52.067
Dad, did you know that your
bones grow three times as fast

10:52.152 --> 10:53.277
during the night?

10:53.361 --> 10:56.030
No, I didn't know that, but I
heard something like that once.

10:56.114 --> 10:57.197
Is that me?
Excellent!

10:57.282 --> 10:59.116
Yeah,
that's you.

10:59.200 --> 11:00.451
Now, is that me?
Yeah.

11:00.535 --> 11:02.328
When we was fishing, right?
Yeah, that's when...

11:02.412 --> 11:04.830
That's beautiful.
Look at the tent.

11:04.914 --> 11:08.500
You know, the fish was a
lot bigger, if I recall.

11:08.585 --> 11:11.879
Well, actually, that was a lot smaller.

11:11.963 --> 11:14.173
Now, anyway, come on.
Hit the bed.

11:14.257 --> 11:16.300
It's time for you to get
healthy and everything.

11:16.384 --> 11:17.551
This is great,
how you do this.

11:17.635 --> 11:19.470
I don't know where
you learned this.

11:19.554 --> 11:22.598
It is something, how this
thing comes out of your fingers.

11:23.433 --> 11:24.808
Oh, my God.

11:26.186 --> 11:27.561
Oh, my God.

11:30.273 --> 11:31.565
Who's this?

11:33.276 --> 11:36.612
That's Madame Dupont,
my French teacher.

11:37.030 --> 11:38.280
Really?

11:41.409 --> 11:43.535
Yeah, she looks French, sure.

11:43.620 --> 11:45.954
I wouldn't show this
to your mother,

11:46.039 --> 11:48.540
'cause she don't
understand French too good.

11:48.625 --> 11:51.710
God. Better cover
that one up.

11:51.795 --> 11:53.629
Well, champ,
it's bedtime.

11:54.464 --> 11:56.965
Hey, you know what?
I know some French talk.

11:57.425 --> 11:58.550
Knock, knock.

11:58.635 --> 11:59.635
Who's there?

11:59.719 --> 12:00.886
Madame.

12:00.970 --> 12:02.054
Madame who?

12:02.138 --> 12:03.889
My damn foot's
caught in the door.

12:03.973 --> 12:05.224
That's an old joke.

12:05.308 --> 12:07.935
What do you want from me?
I'm trying. You know?

12:08.019 --> 12:09.978
I don't know all the
good things, you know?

12:10.063 --> 12:12.523
Hey, what's this?

12:12.607 --> 12:13.690
What?

12:14.567 --> 12:16.318
Look what I
found in your ear.

12:16.403 --> 12:18.779
Russian money.
Money ears!

12:19.489 --> 12:22.658
All right. Anyway, listen,
kid, you gotta get some sleep.

12:22.742 --> 12:24.118
Dad?
Yeah?

12:24.494 --> 12:27.371
Today when you said having me
was like being born again...

12:27.455 --> 12:29.373
Yeah?
What did you mean?

12:30.125 --> 12:34.503
Well, you know, when you come
up like I did, and you got like

12:36.005 --> 12:39.633
three square meals of zero
a day, you know what I mean?

12:39.717 --> 12:41.927
You got the A side of life
and the B side of life.

12:42.011 --> 12:45.764
I'm, like, on the B side, but
you, you got all the breaks.

12:45.849 --> 12:50.102
So, when I see you having all
these things that I didn't have,

12:50.186 --> 12:53.355
I, like,
live through your eyes.

12:53.440 --> 12:54.523
I enjoy it a little bit.

12:54.607 --> 12:57.985
It's like having
it all over again.

12:58.069 --> 12:59.361
That's nice.

13:00.613 --> 13:02.739
Hey, look at my face.

13:02.824 --> 13:04.241
Do I look like a raccoon?

13:05.243 --> 13:06.243
A little bit.

13:06.327 --> 13:08.328
Yeah, like Rocky Raccoon?
Yeah, a little bit.

13:08.413 --> 13:10.372
No!
Yeah, you do a little.

13:10.540 --> 13:11.498
Really?

13:11.583 --> 13:15.502
Hey, if you think I look bad, you
ought to see the other guy's knuckles.

13:17.297 --> 13:20.090
Anyway, yo, good night.

13:20.175 --> 13:21.383
Okay, kid?
Night.

13:23.678 --> 13:25.053
Dad?
Yo.

13:26.598 --> 13:27.890
Glad you're home.

13:28.308 --> 13:30.184
Thanks. I appreciate it.

13:30.852 --> 13:32.519
And we'll play tomorrow,
okay?

13:33.271 --> 13:34.938
Maybe you can show me
your English teacher.

13:35.023 --> 13:36.315
She's pretty hot, too.

13:36.399 --> 13:37.983
Nah!
Yeah.

13:38.067 --> 13:39.485
Good night, kid.

13:39.569 --> 13:41.403
You deserve the worst
for what you did.

13:42.572 --> 13:44.656
Paulie, it wasn't your
money. It was Rocky's money.

13:44.741 --> 13:46.492
You gonna be hysterical?
You cost us everything.

13:46.576 --> 13:48.494
That's what I need.
It was a mistake.

13:48.578 --> 13:51.330
You think I thought this
all was gonna happen?

13:51.414 --> 13:53.081
Don't you walk
away from me.

13:53.166 --> 13:55.792
You just gave up
our life!

13:56.252 --> 13:58.587
And you think it's
like some stupid thing?

13:58.671 --> 14:01.340
Paulie! Paulie, do
you know what you did?

14:01.424 --> 14:02.883
Do you know the
seriousness of what you did?

14:02.967 --> 14:04.009
I understand it!

14:04.093 --> 14:05.427
Do you?
Then answer me!

14:05.512 --> 14:07.387
I understand
the whole freaking thing!

14:07.472 --> 14:10.849
I understand it! Your
accountant's the crook, not me!

14:10.934 --> 14:12.643
I did what I
thought was right.

14:12.727 --> 14:14.144
So, now, don't blame me for nothing.

14:14.229 --> 14:16.605
I want to murder the bum
worse than anybody.

14:16.689 --> 14:18.690
Hey, Adrian,
what's wrong?

14:18.775 --> 14:20.359
Look what you done now.

14:20.443 --> 14:21.527
She's dumping
everything on me.

14:21.611 --> 14:23.362
Come on, Paulie. Don't
turn this around on me.

14:23.446 --> 14:24.655
Come on, what'd you do, Paulie?

14:24.739 --> 14:26.198
He gave power...

14:26.282 --> 14:28.242
Power of attorney to
our accountant. What?

14:28.326 --> 14:32.162
Gave... I just didn't gave
anything to nobody, huh?

14:32.247 --> 14:33.330
He sent a letter!

14:33.414 --> 14:35.832
He says we're gonna be in Russia
a couple of months. He says,

14:35.917 --> 14:38.377
"And I need Rocky
to sign a tax extension!"

14:38.461 --> 14:42.214
Not an extension! That was
a power of attorney, Paulie!

14:42.298 --> 14:44.800
He's the thief!
I need alcohol.

14:45.552 --> 14:48.303
Rocky, on my eyes, I never
stole a freaking dime.

14:49.305 --> 14:51.473
Adrian,
what's happening here?

14:52.058 --> 14:53.058
It's gone.

14:53.142 --> 14:54.268
What's gone?

14:54.352 --> 14:55.978
The money.
The money.

14:56.062 --> 14:57.938
Everything.
It's all gone.

14:58.648 --> 15:00.232
The piece of paper
Paulie had you sign

15:00.316 --> 15:03.068
wasn't a request for an
extension on your tax returns.

15:03.152 --> 15:07.155
It was a blanket power of attorney
in favor of the accountant,

15:07.240 --> 15:10.242
who was involved in some very
high-priced commercial real estate.

15:10.326 --> 15:12.411
He thought he could flip
it quick, take his profit,

15:12.495 --> 15:14.538
have your money back
before you knew it was gone.

15:14.622 --> 15:17.416
And unfortunately for you
and everybody in this room,

15:17.500 --> 15:20.252
his deals fell through
because the market dried up.

15:20.336 --> 15:21.878
And you lost millions.

15:21.963 --> 15:23.755
So, what are you saying? There
ain't nothing I can do about it?

15:23.840 --> 15:26.341
I'm doing plenty. I've filed
eight criminal acts against him,

15:26.426 --> 15:29.177
but you've got tremendous debt
payment on this property, Rocky.

15:29.262 --> 15:31.430
You didn't pay your tax
returns in six years,

15:31.514 --> 15:33.724
and the mortgage on your house
hasn't been paid in months.

15:33.808 --> 15:37.269
Wait, we didn't have a mortgage.
Our house was fully paid for.

15:37.353 --> 15:38.812
Don't take it from me.
Ask him.

15:38.896 --> 15:42.608
Apparently not. There's nearly
$400,000 still outstanding.

15:42.692 --> 15:44.484
The only thing you have
that's not encumbered

15:44.569 --> 15:46.528
is a gymnasium that was
willed to your son

15:46.613 --> 15:49.615
by a Mickey Goldmill
in 1982.

15:49.699 --> 15:52.284
You can sell some things.
Remember those commercials you did?

15:52.368 --> 15:54.745
You know, Paulie, I ain't
no commercial kind of guy.

15:54.829 --> 15:56.663
I'm a fighter.
It's what I do for a living.

15:56.748 --> 15:59.249
Nah, it's just as well. We
couldn't get any sponsors.

15:59.334 --> 16:01.293
With the investigation
of the accountant,

16:01.377 --> 16:03.587
out pops a criminal record
of Rocky's for assault

16:03.671 --> 16:05.213
in connection
with loan sharking.

16:05.298 --> 16:07.591
But that was a long time
ago. He didn't know what...

16:07.675 --> 16:09.176
Why not a couple more fights?

16:09.260 --> 16:10.469
With your
popularity right now,

16:10.553 --> 16:12.012
you could be out of
this thing in no time.

16:12.096 --> 16:13.138
No, he's retiring.

16:13.222 --> 16:14.640
Rocko, fighting's the ticket.

16:14.724 --> 16:16.642
I said he's retired!

16:16.726 --> 16:18.560
Paulie, we're here
because of you!

16:19.187 --> 16:21.438
I'm not taking
the heat for all this.

16:21.522 --> 16:23.148
I thought I was
doing smart business.

16:23.232 --> 16:25.233
You thought you
did smart business?

16:25.318 --> 16:26.276
Hey, you...
Me?

16:26.402 --> 16:28.278
What are you talking about me?
The accountant was your choice!

16:28.404 --> 16:29.696
My choice? You should
have known he was a thief,

16:29.781 --> 16:30.781
but you're never awake

16:30.865 --> 16:33.450
because you live in this fairy-tale
world where the air don't move.

16:33.576 --> 16:35.410
Paulie... You're like a
season that don't change!

16:35.495 --> 16:36.828
Hey, you don't
talk to her like this.

16:36.913 --> 16:38.538
I'm not no tomato
can you kick around!

16:38.623 --> 16:39.956
Paulie, no!
Yeah!

16:40.083 --> 16:42.417
You call Duke. You tell
him I'll fight Cane.

16:42.502 --> 16:44.169
I don't care,
anywhere, anytime.

16:44.295 --> 16:45.462
No, Rocky.
If that's what you want,

16:45.546 --> 16:46.672
I'll get on it right away.

16:46.756 --> 16:47.839
No. No.

16:47.924 --> 16:48.924
Rocky, Rocky, please.

16:49.008 --> 16:51.802
We can't go down like this. A couple
of fights, we're out of trouble, Adrian.

16:51.886 --> 16:53.011
Yeah, but you said you wouldn't.

16:53.096 --> 16:54.221
No, I didn't say anything.

16:54.305 --> 16:55.555
Look, did we come
this far to lose it?

16:55.640 --> 16:57.224
Well, you know, you
have to see a doctor.

16:57.308 --> 16:58.684
Adrian, I don't need to see no doctor.

16:58.768 --> 16:59.810
I need to get
a promoter.

16:59.894 --> 17:00.977
Hey, you know, you gotta see a doctor.

17:01.104 --> 17:02.896
If he says it's all right, I'll
support anything you wanna do.

17:02.980 --> 17:04.146
I gotta fight, okay?

17:04.232 --> 17:05.691
I got problems.
I gotta fight.

17:06.567 --> 17:08.318
Will you do it for me?

17:10.613 --> 17:12.239
All right, for you.

17:13.199 --> 17:16.201
Because of the continuous
violent blows to the head,

17:16.285 --> 17:18.453
you've developed a condition
particular to boxers

17:18.538 --> 17:20.872
called cavum
septum pellucidum,

17:20.957 --> 17:24.376
which is a hole in the membrane
separating the ventricles.

17:24.460 --> 17:28.255
The brain's surface neurons in this
area have also been traumatized.

17:28.339 --> 17:30.841
Excuse me, Doctor.
Simply stated, Mr. Balboa,

17:30.925 --> 17:34.052
it means that you've suffered
some damage to the brain.

17:34.137 --> 17:36.054
How long until he recovers?

17:36.139 --> 17:37.764
The effects
are irreversible.

17:39.016 --> 17:42.728
I... Rocky,
you have to retire.

17:42.812 --> 17:44.146
Adrian,
I don't want to retire.

17:44.230 --> 17:45.856
You know, this ain't
the time to retire.

17:45.940 --> 17:48.525
No, not in here,
not in no office.

17:49.152 --> 17:52.904
I just fought the best fight of
my life. I just did that, you know,

17:54.365 --> 17:56.908
and all I need
is a couple more.

17:56.993 --> 17:59.453
No, Rocky, you suffered
severe brain trauma.

17:59.537 --> 18:01.246
Well, he could be wrong.
Anybody could be wrong.

18:01.330 --> 18:02.330
I don't think he is.

18:02.415 --> 18:04.583
He ain't God. Look, Adrian,
only God ain't wrong.

18:04.667 --> 18:06.960
Hey, Rocky,
this is what's good for you.

18:07.044 --> 18:08.754
All I need is
a couple easy ones, right?

18:08.838 --> 18:11.214
Not with the way it is. You
can't get licensed in any state.

18:11.299 --> 18:13.675
He can't get
licensed anyway, Doctor?

18:13.760 --> 18:14.885
That is correct.

18:15.511 --> 18:17.971
Rocky,
do you love me?

18:20.183 --> 18:22.100
Yeah, I love you.
Why you ask that?

18:22.185 --> 18:24.770
Because if you
love somebody,

18:24.854 --> 18:26.938
you live with them,
you live for them.

18:27.023 --> 18:29.065
You don't gamble
with a life.

18:29.150 --> 18:32.110
Rocky, I don't care
about the money. It's you.

18:33.237 --> 18:35.030
That's all that matters.

18:36.657 --> 18:40.702
Please. We'll be okay. We'll be fine.

18:44.624 --> 18:45.874
No one's gotta know...

18:47.919 --> 18:49.044
Uh...

18:51.297 --> 18:53.256
No one has to know,
doctor, right?

18:53.341 --> 18:55.217
It'll be
strictly confidential.

18:59.972 --> 19:01.306
Thank you.

19:20.910 --> 19:23.829
May we hear
our next bid, please?

19:23.913 --> 19:25.163
Are you done?

19:26.374 --> 19:27.499
Sold.

19:30.753 --> 19:33.880
Moving along, ladies and
gentlemen, item number 46.

19:33.965 --> 19:36.258
Hey, kid.
Bike's been sold.

19:37.093 --> 19:39.678
Hey, bike's been sold.
Get off the bike. Come on.

19:43.766 --> 19:47.769
We have an opening bid.
$25,000 is the bid.

19:49.313 --> 19:51.565
Don't worry about it.
We've been down before.

19:51.899 --> 19:53.233
I'll get it all back.

19:53.317 --> 19:55.443
We just gotta stick together,
all right?

19:55.528 --> 19:56.862
Home team.

19:56.946 --> 19:57.946
Yeah, right.

19:58.030 --> 19:59.155
Sold.

19:59.782 --> 20:01.783
Come on, you know,
Mickey used to say

20:01.868 --> 20:04.244
a fight ain't over
till you heard the bell.

20:04.328 --> 20:06.037
We ain't heard
a bell yet, have we?

20:06.122 --> 20:10.083
Rocky Balboa's boxing gloves
from his first heavyweight fight.

20:27.727 --> 20:29.060
Rocky?

20:30.730 --> 20:32.105
Hey, it still fits.

20:35.151 --> 20:37.652
Why you wearing
those clothes?

20:37.737 --> 20:40.739
I was just going through some of
the stuff up there, and I found 'em,

20:40.823 --> 20:43.116
and they feel kind of
comfortable, you know?

20:43.200 --> 20:46.369
Well, I was looking all
over for you downstairs.

20:46.454 --> 20:47.412
It's kind of
depressing.

20:47.496 --> 20:50.206
Yeah, I know
what you mean.

20:50.291 --> 20:53.418
What's this
doing in your ear?

20:53.502 --> 20:54.628
What? Oh, God.

20:54.712 --> 20:56.212
Remember these?

20:56.923 --> 20:58.757
I... Yeah.

20:58.841 --> 21:00.592
Go ahead.
You...

21:00.801 --> 21:01.801
I remember when
you took them off.

21:01.886 --> 21:02.928
That's right.

21:03.012 --> 21:05.847
First time I ever
kissed you, remember?

21:06.140 --> 21:07.349
Kiss me.

21:09.185 --> 21:12.938
Adrian, I want to go out
for a little bit, you know?

21:13.022 --> 21:14.773
Just take a little walk.

21:14.857 --> 21:16.441
I just wanna
feel better, but...

21:16.525 --> 21:19.402
Hey, could you talk to
the kid? 'Cause he's...

21:19.820 --> 21:20.820
He's really taking
this hard, you know?

21:20.905 --> 21:21.988
Sure.

21:22.114 --> 21:23.114
Okay?

21:23.991 --> 21:25.033
Where you going?

21:25.117 --> 21:26.910
I thought I'd go to Andy's.

22:11.872 --> 22:13.790
How you doing, Mick?

23:24.528 --> 23:25.904
Slip the jab.

23:27.865 --> 23:29.324
Slip the jab.
Slip the jab.

23:29.408 --> 23:30.825
Slip the jab,
will ya?

23:32.411 --> 23:33.495
Slip the jab!

23:36.415 --> 23:38.541
That's right.
That's it.

23:38.626 --> 23:40.376
Hey, I didn't
hear no bell!

23:40.461 --> 23:41.669
Okay.

23:42.505 --> 23:43.922
All right. That's right.

23:44.006 --> 23:47.592
Slip the jab.
That's it. Mentalize.

23:47.676 --> 23:49.803
See that bum
in front of you.

23:49.887 --> 23:53.014
You see yourself doing right,
and you do right.

23:54.141 --> 23:56.101
That's pretty.
That's very pretty.

23:56.769 --> 23:58.436
Time!

23:58.521 --> 24:01.940
Come here, Rock. My God,
you're ready, ain't you?

24:02.024 --> 24:03.566
And Apollo won't
know what hit him.

24:03.651 --> 24:07.821
You're gonna roll over him like
a bulldozer, an Italian bulldozer.

24:08.489 --> 24:10.281
You know, kid,
I know how you feel

24:10.366 --> 24:12.367
about this fight
that's coming up.

24:12.785 --> 24:15.120
Because
I was young once, too.

24:16.163 --> 24:17.622
And I tell you something.

24:18.916 --> 24:24.420
Well, if you wasn't here, I
probably wouldn't be alive today.

24:24.964 --> 24:27.048
The fact that you're here

24:27.133 --> 24:29.968
and doing as well
as you're doing gives me,

24:30.052 --> 24:33.721
what do you call it, a
motivization to stay alive?

24:34.348 --> 24:36.933
'Cause I think that
people die sometimes

24:37.017 --> 24:38.560
when they don't
wanna live no more.

24:39.061 --> 24:41.229
"Nature's smarter
than people think. "

24:41.313 --> 24:43.648
And nature is smarter
than people think.

24:43.732 --> 24:46.901
Little by little, we lose our
friends, we lose everything.

24:46.986 --> 24:50.071
We keep losing and
losing till we say,

24:51.073 --> 24:53.158
you know, "What the hell
am I living around here for?

24:53.242 --> 24:55.326
"I got no reason to go on. "

24:56.745 --> 25:01.207
But with you, kid, boy,
I got a reason to go on,

25:02.001 --> 25:06.004
and I'm gonna stay alive, and
I will watch you make good.

25:06.422 --> 25:07.505
"And I'll never leave you. "

25:07.590 --> 25:08.882
And I'll never leave you

25:08.966 --> 25:10.425
until that happens.

25:10.926 --> 25:15.096
'Cause when I leave you, you'll
not only know how to fight,

25:15.931 --> 25:19.184
you'll be able to take care of
yourself outside the ring, too.

25:19.268 --> 25:20.351
Is that okay?

25:20.436 --> 25:21.436
It's okay.

25:22.271 --> 25:23.980
Okay.

25:24.064 --> 25:25.565
Now, I got
a little gift for you.

25:25.649 --> 25:27.525
Mick, you... Now, wait a
minute. Wait a minute now.

25:27.610 --> 25:28.568
Wait a minute.

25:28.652 --> 25:29.819
Really, I don't
need nothing.

25:29.904 --> 25:32.447
Look at this. See that?

25:32.615 --> 25:35.241
This is the favorite thing
that I have on this Earth,

25:36.535 --> 25:39.037
and Rocky Marciano
give me that.

25:39.830 --> 25:41.915
You know what it was?
His cufflink.

25:43.626 --> 25:45.752
And now I'm
giving it to you.

25:47.004 --> 25:49.505
And it is gonna be
like a...

25:50.466 --> 25:53.134
Like an angel on
your shoulder, see?

25:53.928 --> 25:58.640
If you ever get hurt, and you
feel that you're going down,

25:59.558 --> 26:02.685
this little angel is
gonna whisper in your ear.

26:02.770 --> 26:06.606
He's gonna say, "Get
up, you son of a bitch,

26:08.025 --> 26:09.609
"'cause Mickey loves you. "

26:10.319 --> 26:11.402
Okay?

26:13.072 --> 26:14.364
Thanks, Mick.
All right.

26:14.448 --> 26:16.532
I love you, too.

26:17.451 --> 26:18.826
Go after 'em, kid.

26:19.995 --> 26:21.621
Go after 'em.
Thanks.

26:26.460 --> 26:28.002
You was the angel.

26:29.088 --> 26:30.338
There it is.

26:30.798 --> 26:32.257
What happened to
his other cufflink?

26:32.341 --> 26:34.425
I don't know.
He only give me one.

26:35.344 --> 26:37.178
He gave it to some bum.

26:55.698 --> 26:59.534
Take you back Take
you back Take you back

27:00.452 --> 27:02.120
Take you back

27:02.204 --> 27:04.831
From the streets
Cometh a man

27:04.915 --> 27:07.041
A fighter
Doin' the best that I can

27:07.167 --> 27:09.627
To survive Yes, and it's
survival of the fittest

27:09.712 --> 27:12.255
Strive for what is mine
The Lord is my witness

27:12.339 --> 27:14.132
Many believe
in what they see

27:14.216 --> 27:15.174
And I wonder

27:15.259 --> 27:16.426
What do they see in me?

27:16.510 --> 27:19.012
For a man,
he must walk alone

27:19.096 --> 27:20.138
To grow

27:20.222 --> 27:21.472
And to bring
his knowledge home

27:21.557 --> 27:23.891
School of hard knocks
is my alma mater

27:23.976 --> 27:26.269
Lady luck,
you know that I got her

27:26.353 --> 27:27.770
Fame and fortune
never a concern

27:27.855 --> 27:29.314
Don't worry about these.

27:29.398 --> 27:31.065
All right.
Let's go, Paulie.

27:32.026 --> 27:33.901
I really can't believe it.
This kid's taking this too good.

27:34.028 --> 27:35.653
Need a hand, champ?
No, I got it.

27:35.738 --> 27:38.281
Hey, Rock. It's good I
kept the place, right?

27:38.365 --> 27:39.824
How you doing?
It saves money.

27:39.908 --> 27:41.659
Yeah.
Hey, get back.

27:41.744 --> 27:42.744
Right?

27:43.245 --> 27:46.831
A little aluminum on the
front, hey, it's a winner.

27:50.377 --> 27:51.461
Thank you.

27:53.005 --> 27:55.923
Welcome back, Rocky!
We missed ya!

27:57.468 --> 27:59.761
It's only... It's only
temporary, you know?

28:00.512 --> 28:02.055
Come on inside.

28:04.433 --> 28:05.433
Thanks.

28:13.108 --> 28:14.901
Hello?
Mrs. Balboa?

28:14.985 --> 28:16.694
George Washington Duke here.

28:16.779 --> 28:17.862
Yes?

28:17.946 --> 28:19.739
Mrs. Balboa, can you hear it?

28:19.823 --> 28:22.033
Listen close,
you must be able to hear it.

28:23.243 --> 28:24.243
Hear what?

28:24.328 --> 28:25.870
The sound of
the parade going by,

28:25.954 --> 28:28.081
of opportunity knocking.

28:28.165 --> 28:30.249
I mean, what's it gonna take
to get you people to realize

28:30.334 --> 28:33.711
I'm giving you a chance to
pull yourselves together again?

28:33.796 --> 28:36.130
Let me handle your husband's
career and the money will pour in.

28:36.215 --> 28:38.674
You can start living
like human beings again.

28:39.426 --> 28:41.677
Listen, Mr. Duke, we're
living like human beings.

28:41.762 --> 28:43.388
You ought to
try it sometime.

28:44.932 --> 28:46.724
You leave my husband alone.

28:50.437 --> 28:51.604
Women.

28:58.821 --> 29:00.530
When'd you
start that?

29:01.156 --> 29:03.533
I don't know. It's like a
bad habit that comes back.

29:03.617 --> 29:05.034
But, hey, listen.

29:05.119 --> 29:08.246
We ain't talking about me,
we're talking about you, right?

29:08.330 --> 29:09.372
Hey, Rocky,
how you doing, man?

29:09.456 --> 29:10.415
Yo. How you doing?

29:10.499 --> 29:11.833
Good to see you back
in the neighborhood.

29:11.917 --> 29:13.209
Yeah. Thank you.
It's great to be back.

29:13.293 --> 29:14.877
You know, you're
real smart in school,

29:14.962 --> 29:17.130
but you gotta be smart
on the street, too, see?

29:17.214 --> 29:18.423
How do you mean?

29:18.507 --> 29:20.216
Well, you gotta know
who the players are

29:20.300 --> 29:22.135
and, like, who you're
talking to around here.

29:22.219 --> 29:24.595
Watch out for the scammers.
Everybody's gonna try to scam.

29:24.680 --> 29:26.597
What's a scam?
Ask your father.

29:26.682 --> 29:29.142
Well, a scam is
like a hustle.

29:29.643 --> 29:30.601
He don't get it.

29:30.686 --> 29:32.103
Well, you know, like
a hustle's related to...

29:32.187 --> 29:33.312
Rocky?
Yeah?

29:33.397 --> 29:35.106
Rocky, remember me?
I'm Bubba's mother.

29:35.190 --> 29:36.190
Yeah.

29:36.275 --> 29:37.942
You used to use his
head for a punching bag.

29:38.026 --> 29:39.026
Yeah, he had
a nice head.

29:39.111 --> 29:40.278
Welcome back.

29:41.196 --> 29:43.823
So, anyway, like a hustle's
related to a con, you know?

29:43.907 --> 29:45.908
He don't get it.
A deception.

29:46.034 --> 29:47.034
Excuse me?

29:47.119 --> 29:48.202
You're saying
beware of deceptions.

29:48.287 --> 29:50.329
Yeah, that's good.
Absolutely.

29:50.414 --> 29:51.747
You're very smart,
you know?

29:52.916 --> 29:56.502
Hey, ain't this where the
Atomic Hoagie shop used to be?

29:56.587 --> 29:58.421
I'm new here,
Dad.

29:58.714 --> 30:01.007
This neighborhood's coming
down with tooth decay.

30:01.091 --> 30:02.508
It's called
urban blight.

30:02.593 --> 30:03.634
Yeah?

30:04.219 --> 30:07.388
I'll tell you something, this
place is blight new, you know?

30:07.806 --> 30:09.765
I think a little aluminum
siding and some paint,

30:09.850 --> 30:12.018
this place could be okay
again. What do you think?

30:12.102 --> 30:13.978
I don't know. Anyway, we're
gonna be late for school. Come on.

30:14.062 --> 30:16.981
Hey, Paulie, I wanna talk to
the kid private, like, you know,

30:17.065 --> 30:18.107
man to smaller man,
all right?

30:18.192 --> 30:19.400
Right.
Like I got no feelings.

30:19.485 --> 30:20.485
Come on, Paulie.

30:20.569 --> 30:21.694
That's how wars start.

30:21.778 --> 30:23.279
Relax, would you?

30:23.363 --> 30:25.281
So, anyway, you know, everybody's
got an angle, you know?

30:25.365 --> 30:27.325
Yo, tough break, Rock.
Yeah.

30:27.409 --> 30:29.160
Everybody's got
a hustle, you know?

30:29.244 --> 30:30.369
See, like these kids around here,

30:30.454 --> 30:32.038
they got street brains,
you see?

30:32.122 --> 30:33.164
That's how they live.

30:33.248 --> 30:34.707
These kids ain't like...
Listen to me.

30:34.791 --> 30:37.752
They ain't like no personalities
that you growed up with.

30:37.836 --> 30:40.463
So you gotta stay very,
very sharp around here.

30:40.547 --> 30:42.131
I intend to.

30:42.216 --> 30:45.760
"Intend. " You know, sometimes
you make me feel very stupid.

30:46.470 --> 30:48.012
Why?
Why?

30:48.096 --> 30:50.014
'Cause you're smarter
than me, and that's a fact.

30:50.098 --> 30:51.682
No, I'm not.
Yeah, you are.

30:51.767 --> 30:53.851
It's like every day
you learn something new,

30:53.936 --> 30:55.853
and every day I
forget something new,

30:55.938 --> 30:57.688
but listen.
Listen to me.

30:57.773 --> 31:00.399
We're in this thing together,
so if you can figure out any way

31:00.484 --> 31:02.860
on how to fix things up,
don't be afraid to tell me,

31:02.945 --> 31:05.905
'cause we gotta stick
together, 'cause what are we?

31:05.989 --> 31:07.698
What?

31:07.783 --> 31:08.950
What are we?

31:09.701 --> 31:10.952
Oh, oh...
Home team.

31:11.036 --> 31:12.787
Home team! You know, you got that right.

31:12.871 --> 31:14.539
You know, I used to go to
this school when I was a kid.

31:14.623 --> 31:15.623
You know. Nice bricks.

31:15.707 --> 31:17.708
Used to have good milk
at lunch and everything.

31:17.793 --> 31:18.876
It was real tough then,

31:18.961 --> 31:21.587
but I think you can
handle it, don't you think?

31:21.672 --> 31:24.757
No way, you don't even know
what you're talking about.

31:24.841 --> 31:26.759
If you went here,
I can go here.

31:27.844 --> 31:30.179
I'm not scared, really.

31:30.264 --> 31:31.389
Really?

31:32.474 --> 31:34.892
Well, I guess
I'm a little scared.

31:34.977 --> 31:36.352
But that's normal,
don't you think?

31:36.436 --> 31:38.563
Yeah. You know,
I had 72 fights coming up,

31:38.647 --> 31:40.231
and every one of 'em
I was scared.

31:40.315 --> 31:43.734
So, yeah, you know,
that's real, real normal.

31:46.738 --> 31:47.738
I'll see ya later.

31:47.823 --> 31:48.906
Okay, kid.

31:48.991 --> 31:50.408
Here's the front door.

31:51.910 --> 31:53.828
Okay. Hey, wait!
What's this?

31:53.912 --> 31:54.912
What's...

31:56.164 --> 31:57.206
Goodness gracious.

31:57.291 --> 31:58.749
Where'd this come from?

31:58.834 --> 32:01.961
It's a strange place to stash
your lunch money, don't you think?

32:02.045 --> 32:04.255
It's just a lunch joke, you know?

32:04.339 --> 32:05.381
Thanks, Dad.

32:05.465 --> 32:07.383
Okay, listen.
I'll see you later.

32:08.176 --> 32:10.553
Remember, Daddy loves you.
You're number one.

32:10.637 --> 32:11.762
Home team!

32:11.847 --> 32:14.265
Just be nice, right?
You'll be okay.

32:15.267 --> 32:17.935
And don't mess with
nobody's girlfriend.

32:18.020 --> 32:19.562
They don't like
that around here.

32:26.486 --> 32:28.613
You know, Paulie, I'm
really worried about the kid.

32:28.697 --> 32:30.448
You know, he ain't
used to living like this.

32:30.532 --> 32:32.283
He don't know
the streets or nothing.

32:32.367 --> 32:34.952
And that school, I know
exactly what's gonna happen.

32:35.037 --> 32:37.997
Some wise guy's gonna come
up to him 'cause he's my kid.

32:38.081 --> 32:40.124
He's just gonna come out
and try to bang him out,

32:40.208 --> 32:43.127
give him a cheap shot,
you know? I mean... Jeez.

32:43.211 --> 32:44.295
Mr. Balboa?
Yeah?

32:44.379 --> 32:45.504
How you doing?
My name's Tommy Gunn.

32:45.589 --> 32:46.672
Yeah, how
you doing?

32:46.757 --> 32:48.591
Well, with a name like that,
you better be tough.

32:48.675 --> 32:50.301
Yeah, very true.
It ain't easy.

32:50.385 --> 32:51.761
Anyway, I come
from Oklahoma.

32:51.845 --> 32:52.845
Welcome.

32:52.929 --> 32:54.138
I have an amateur's
record of 45-to-one.

32:54.222 --> 32:56.223
And I turned pro at 18,
and I had eight fights.

32:56.308 --> 32:58.100
You're a fighter?
Yeah, I'm a fighter.

32:58.185 --> 33:01.062
And now that I'm 20, I'd just
like to show you what I got.

33:01.188 --> 33:02.980
Well, I... I mean, I've
saved up about 400 bucks.

33:03.065 --> 33:04.482
Mr. Rocky Balboa. I could
pay you for training.

33:04.566 --> 33:05.608
Yeah... What?

33:05.692 --> 33:07.401
Excuse me, young man,
I have some business here.

33:07.486 --> 33:08.653
What, is he lost or what?
Thank you.

33:08.737 --> 33:09.945
Good to see you again,
friend. How you doing?

33:10.030 --> 33:10.988
Yeah. How you doing?

33:11.073 --> 33:12.657
My health is fine. What
more could a man ask for?

33:12.741 --> 33:13.699
Money and hair.

33:13.784 --> 33:14.992
Listen, I gotta
go to work now.

33:15.077 --> 33:16.160
What? Where? Here? In a sweatbox?

33:16.244 --> 33:17.244
Yeah.

33:17.329 --> 33:18.454
Can't be good
for the image.

33:18.538 --> 33:19.955
Urban light.
What are you gonna do?

33:20.040 --> 33:21.499
Hey, Rocky, Rocky...
What'd you say?

33:21.583 --> 33:23.584
Urban light. It's
"blight. " Urban blight.

33:23.710 --> 33:24.835
Rock, George would
like you to consider

33:24.920 --> 33:26.253
putting on those
damn gloves again.

33:26.338 --> 33:28.005
It's a hell of
a payday.

33:28.090 --> 33:29.507
Well, you know,
I'm officially expired.

33:29.591 --> 33:30.966
No, you do have
marquee value.

33:31.051 --> 33:32.843
You put butts in the
buckets, asses in the seats.

33:32.928 --> 33:34.512
A businessman with
any sort of brain

33:34.596 --> 33:36.847
don't retire when he can
still pull in the bread, baby.

33:36.932 --> 33:39.058
'Cause only in America do we
get these kind of opportunities.

33:39.142 --> 33:41.477
Union Cane's going for
the title on the 14th.

33:41.561 --> 33:43.187
Yeah, here's some
tickets. Be our guests.

33:43.271 --> 33:44.397
We have a strong
feeling about this one.

33:44.481 --> 33:45.606
Think he's gonna take it.

33:45.691 --> 33:46.857
That's the time
to challenge.

33:46.942 --> 33:48.984
Because people
love comebacks,

33:49.069 --> 33:51.362
and there's nothing in the
boxing business more commercial

33:51.446 --> 33:52.697
than a long-shot comeback

33:52.781 --> 33:55.157
of a down-on-his-luck,
pure snow-white underdog.

33:55.242 --> 33:56.867
Now, like your
Mark Twain once said,

33:56.952 --> 33:59.412
"Virtue has never been
as respectable as money. "

33:59.496 --> 34:00.955
Who's Twain?
He was a painter.

34:01.039 --> 34:03.666
Look, simply put,
you're the great white hope.

34:03.750 --> 34:04.792
You mean great white dope.
No, forget it.

34:04.876 --> 34:05.876
No, no,
Rock, Rock...

34:05.961 --> 34:07.044
I ain't emotionally
involved in boxing...

34:07.129 --> 34:08.963
Hey, hold it.
Hold the bullshit.

34:09.047 --> 34:11.047
I know what the problem is.
You think I was born yesterday?

34:11.132 --> 34:12.425
Merlin, show him
the paper.

34:12.509 --> 34:14.217
What paper? Now, this
is your medical report.

34:14.302 --> 34:16.344
It's not so good, but
we can work around it.

34:16.429 --> 34:17.388
Where'd you get this?

34:17.472 --> 34:18.723
It really doesn't matter,
does it, Rock?

34:18.806 --> 34:20.725
You agree to fight Cane,
and George here can guarantee

34:20.809 --> 34:22.268
you get licensed in any
country around the world.

34:22.351 --> 34:23.978
Guaranteed.
You can do this?

34:24.062 --> 34:25.062
No problem.

34:25.147 --> 34:27.022
His comeback's in the bag
and worth millions.

34:27.107 --> 34:29.483
The time is hot, the
deal is hot. Caliente!

34:29.568 --> 34:31.360
We could use one more payday. I agree!

34:31.445 --> 34:32.695
Adrian, where'd
you come from?

34:32.779 --> 34:33.946
What do you
think you're going?

34:34.030 --> 34:36.197
Mrs. Balboa just appeared.
This woman is magic.

34:36.283 --> 34:37.742
Look, I don't think
you're very funny.

34:37.826 --> 34:39.702
Are you trying to talk my
husband into fighting again?

34:39.786 --> 34:41.328
We're talking business,
now, darling.

34:41.413 --> 34:43.330
Do you like feeling hard up?

34:43.415 --> 34:46.041
Do you like reaching in your
pocket and only feeling your leg?

34:46.126 --> 34:48.085
Well, do you?
I didn't think so.

34:48.170 --> 34:50.295
I'm offering you your
last golden opportunity

34:50.380 --> 34:51.672
to dump this loser image.

34:51.757 --> 34:52.965
Who you talking to?

34:53.049 --> 34:54.341
Hey, Adrian, you
weren't working across...

34:54.426 --> 34:57.553
Hey, what the hell are you
two people talking about?

34:57.637 --> 34:59.138
This is
a tremendous opportunity.

34:59.222 --> 35:00.681
Opportunity for who?

35:00.766 --> 35:03.309
For you to make money?
For him to be disabled?

35:03.393 --> 35:05.811
What would you do if the
choices were reversed?

35:06.229 --> 35:08.022
You have to
think about that.

35:08.690 --> 35:11.025
Rocky, they don't
care about you.

35:11.943 --> 35:14.111
You want to get serious?
Let's get serious.

35:14.196 --> 35:16.781
You represent the dreams of the
long shots, the little people.

35:16.865 --> 35:18.407
The never-wills
identify with you,

35:18.492 --> 35:20.451
and identification is
the key to public success.

35:20.535 --> 35:23.454
You're a true champion, a true
product of the people. Now sell it.

35:23.538 --> 35:25.331
Sell it while
there are still buyers.

35:25.415 --> 35:26.415
They ain't
gonna last forever.

35:26.500 --> 35:27.583
You say you're a fighter?
Then fight!

35:27.667 --> 35:29.585
You say you want a
champion's do, then do it

35:29.669 --> 35:32.296
and I'll make you so much
money you could swim in it!

35:32.380 --> 35:34.006
You can swim,
can't you, darling?

35:34.090 --> 35:35.674
What do you say?
Come on. Put it there.

35:35.759 --> 35:37.468
It's time to put some hustle
behind this muscle.

35:37.552 --> 35:40.471
He's done!
He's done fighting!

35:47.646 --> 35:49.897
You're a damn fool.

35:51.358 --> 35:54.318
Maybe we ought to sign Mrs.
Balboa to fight Cane, huh?

35:54.402 --> 35:57.446
Looks like she's the one with
the cojones in the family.

36:00.075 --> 36:03.202
Yo, you don't talk like that
in front of my wife, you know?

36:03.286 --> 36:05.204
That ain't no
park bench, boy.

36:09.292 --> 36:10.626
I'll get him.

36:10.710 --> 36:13.087
Rocky, I'm really sorry.
I didn't wanna...

36:13.171 --> 36:15.089
Hey, you guys
want privacy now?

36:15.173 --> 36:16.298
I'll be upstairs.

36:20.303 --> 36:21.387
Rocky...

36:22.764 --> 36:24.932
Rocky, I'm sorry.
I... I...

36:25.016 --> 36:28.477
But, you know, it just takes one
bad hit, and you could be an invalid.

36:28.562 --> 36:30.437
Well, I feel like
an invalid already, Adrian.

36:30.522 --> 36:31.689
Why'd you gotta
come back here?

36:31.773 --> 36:33.482
You're too smart
for this place here.

36:33.567 --> 36:35.192
I got nothing to do.

36:35.277 --> 36:37.027
Gloria. I called Gloria.

36:37.112 --> 36:39.697
She said, you know, she
could use some part-time help.

36:39.781 --> 36:41.282
Yeah, but why do you
wanna do this, Adrian?

36:41.366 --> 36:43.492
Why do you wanna go back to
the same place you started from?

36:43.577 --> 36:45.578
I gotta do it,
but you don't gotta do it!

36:45.662 --> 36:49.123
I wanted to be there so
I could be close to you.

36:58.508 --> 37:00.050
All right. Yeah.

37:00.135 --> 37:02.303
You know, it's getting a
little cold out here. Maybe...

37:02.387 --> 37:04.096
Okay. Maybe you
better get inside, okay?

37:04.180 --> 37:05.222
I understand.

37:05.307 --> 37:07.099
Are you all right?
What?

37:07.183 --> 37:08.183
Are you all right?

37:08.268 --> 37:09.894
Yeah, I'm all right.
I'm fine.

37:09.978 --> 37:11.729
Hey, it's getting cold, okay?

37:17.986 --> 37:21.780
Yo, Adrian!
Did we ever leave this place?

37:24.576 --> 37:26.327
I don't know!

37:31.833 --> 37:33.626
Hey, mind if I
talk to you now?

37:34.794 --> 37:37.087
My head's
a little busy right now.

37:49.059 --> 37:50.267
George, I don't know
if you're gonna get him.

37:50.352 --> 37:52.061
This guy, Balboa, he don't
think straight anymore.

37:52.145 --> 37:54.063
None of these bums think straight,
but all I need is an angle.

37:54.189 --> 37:55.940
I'll fight Balboa right now. Hey...

37:56.024 --> 37:57.441
I'm better than
Balboa ever was.

37:57.525 --> 37:58.859
Hey, hey!

38:00.362 --> 38:03.322
I own the paper on you, boy.
You will fight who I tell you,

38:03.406 --> 38:06.367
where I tell you, and how
I tell you, you got that?

38:07.827 --> 38:10.371
Don't aggravate the
hand that feeds you, huh?

38:10.538 --> 38:11.538
All right?

38:14.167 --> 38:16.210
None of these bums
think straight.

38:20.882 --> 38:22.383
All I need is a hook.

38:34.229 --> 38:36.355
Hey, ain't you Rocky's kid?

38:37.065 --> 38:38.107
Yeah, you're
Rocky's kid.

38:38.191 --> 38:39.358
You're Rocky's
kid, right?

38:39.442 --> 38:40.484
Yeah, how you doing?

38:40.568 --> 38:42.069
Yeah, I seen your
picture in the paper.

38:42.153 --> 38:43.320
And you know what?

38:43.405 --> 38:45.072
Your old man's a punk.
What?

38:47.200 --> 38:48.242
Get off me!

38:48.326 --> 38:50.202
And what are you
wearing my coat for?

38:50.286 --> 38:51.495
Just leave him alone!

38:51.579 --> 38:52.997
You want a beating too?

38:53.081 --> 38:55.332
Give me my coat! I'm not
kidding around anymore!

38:55.417 --> 38:57.084
You better let him have it.
No way!

39:03.717 --> 39:05.426
Don't get sick now!

39:06.052 --> 39:08.429
Hope you don't
catch cold, rich boy!

39:11.850 --> 39:13.350
Keep it high.
Slipping and sliding.

39:13.435 --> 39:15.352
Slip the jab.
That's it. Come on.

39:15.437 --> 39:16.603
That don't interest you?
This cup?

39:16.688 --> 39:18.939
Rocky drinks out of it
around the house. Ten bucks.

39:19.024 --> 39:20.816
Well, hey, man. How I
know it's the real thing?

39:20.900 --> 39:22.526
Look at the
lip marks, huh?

39:22.610 --> 39:24.486
All right, five bucks.
Five bucks. No more.

39:24.571 --> 39:25.988
You got a deal.
Okay.

39:26.948 --> 39:27.948
Excuse me.

39:28.033 --> 39:29.033
Tommy Gunn!

39:29.117 --> 39:30.367
Is there
someplace I can change?

39:30.452 --> 39:31.952
In there.
Give me the money.

39:32.037 --> 39:35.080
Time! Hey, Richard, Richard,
good friend, listen to me.

39:35.165 --> 39:37.708
If you wanna survive, you gotta
learn to slip the jab, you know?

39:37.792 --> 39:40.669
Keep it high, and hit
and not get hit, you know?

39:40.754 --> 39:41.962
Okay, take off.

39:42.047 --> 39:43.130
Rocko?
Yeah?

39:43.214 --> 39:45.049
Remember Tommy Gunn?
Yeah, yeah.

39:45.133 --> 39:47.676
He says he wants to fight.
I told him to get married.

39:47.761 --> 39:48.844
Why?

39:49.471 --> 39:51.013
That's gym humor, Rocko.

39:51.097 --> 39:52.931
That... Okay.

39:53.349 --> 39:55.642
Hey, let's see what
you got there, kid.

39:56.436 --> 39:57.811
Get married, eh?

39:58.438 --> 40:00.731
Benson,
wanna move a little?

40:00.815 --> 40:01.815
Yeah, all right.

40:01.900 --> 40:03.192
Hey, Paulie,

40:03.276 --> 40:04.818
what's a cojones?

40:05.528 --> 40:10.574
Cojones? Cojones is
Latin for Spanish nuts.

40:10.658 --> 40:11.742
Yo, Rock.

40:11.826 --> 40:13.660
We're ready.
Wonderful.

40:15.163 --> 40:17.956
Hey kid,
you got the headgear?

40:18.041 --> 40:20.084
Nah, I don't
need one. Nah.

40:21.628 --> 40:23.921
He's gonna get his
cojones knocked out.

40:24.464 --> 40:26.256
Okay. Ready, guy?

40:26.341 --> 40:28.634
Benson, go easy, all right?

40:28.718 --> 40:30.636
Sure. Okay, Rock.
Time.

40:31.554 --> 40:34.014
All right.
Just go easy now.

40:34.099 --> 40:35.766
Slip the jab now.

40:37.602 --> 40:38.602
Go easy.

40:38.686 --> 40:39.770
Hey, kid.
What's his name again?

40:39.854 --> 40:41.438
Tommy Gunn.
Tommy Gunn.

40:41.523 --> 40:44.566
Tommy. Whoa!
It ain't no law to duck.

40:44.651 --> 40:45.651
That's it.

40:45.735 --> 40:47.152
Go side to side.
That's it.

40:47.403 --> 40:50.447
Whoa! All right,
that's enough.

40:50.532 --> 40:52.282
Hey, man!
Take it easy, man!

40:52.367 --> 40:53.909
Hey, come on,
you guys, lighten up.

40:53.993 --> 40:55.953
It's called sparring.
Now, go on easy.

40:56.037 --> 40:57.496
Whoa! Hey, hey!

40:57.580 --> 40:59.123
Okay, okay.

40:59.207 --> 41:01.291
Hey, lighten up!
That's it. Tie him up.

41:01.376 --> 41:02.668
That's it.
You smell that, Rocko?

41:02.710 --> 41:04.586
What's that? That's
the odor of opportunity.

41:04.671 --> 41:06.088
Hey, that's it.

41:06.172 --> 41:07.965
What'd I tell you?
Hey, hey! Time!

41:08.049 --> 41:09.883
Hey, that's it! Time!

41:09.968 --> 41:11.385
Chill out, man!
Call time!

41:11.469 --> 41:13.428
Time!
Hey! Hey, back off!

41:13.513 --> 41:15.973
Hey, that's enough!
What's the matter with you?

41:16.057 --> 41:17.558
Tommy, are you crazy
or something?

41:17.642 --> 41:19.059
Hey, what's
the matter with you, man?

41:19.144 --> 41:20.561
Get out of the ring.
I'm sorry.

41:20.645 --> 41:21.645
Get out of the ring.
Cool off, kid.

41:21.729 --> 41:23.021
All right.
I'm sorry about this.

41:23.106 --> 41:25.065
He stinks of opportunity,
Rocko.

41:25.400 --> 41:26.650
Hey, look.

41:26.734 --> 41:28.986
Going easy don't mean
breaking bones, kid.

41:29.070 --> 41:30.654
Man, I'm sorry.
But what do you think?

41:30.738 --> 41:33.323
What do I think? I don't
think you listen too good.

41:33.408 --> 41:36.160
But you, you fight, you brawl
like you was a street fighter,

41:36.244 --> 41:37.452
and I know
something about that.

41:37.537 --> 41:40.414
But this is called boxing.
This ain't no mugging, you know?

41:40.498 --> 41:42.166
I'm sorry. But I know I can do it all.

41:42.250 --> 41:44.418
Yeah? Well, not
on this date, okay?

41:45.461 --> 41:46.545
That's it?

41:46.629 --> 41:48.547
Hey, yo, I gotta work
with these kids here.

41:48.631 --> 41:50.007
You guys get ready.
Come on, one more.

41:50.091 --> 41:51.466
How about you
try to manage me?

41:51.551 --> 41:52.551
Manage?

41:52.635 --> 41:56.263
Yeah, unless you think
I ain't got nothing going.

41:56.347 --> 41:57.973
Man, got nothing going?

41:58.057 --> 42:00.642
Yeah, all right, you got a lot
going. You got a lot of tools.

42:00.727 --> 42:03.353
But I ain't no manager.
I ain't never been...

42:03.438 --> 42:05.355
You know, the gentleman
that owned this place,

42:05.440 --> 42:06.523
that was a manager.

42:06.608 --> 42:10.611
But, me,
I was always the managed guy.

42:11.279 --> 42:13.614
Hey, look.
Good luck, all right?

42:16.367 --> 42:17.826
All right, guys.
Let's go.

42:18.870 --> 42:20.078
Come on,
move around.

42:22.123 --> 42:23.874
That's it. Nice.

42:36.846 --> 42:38.305
All right, you guys, come on.

42:38.389 --> 42:40.140
No cheap shots.
Move it around.

42:47.732 --> 42:49.233
How you doing?

42:50.109 --> 42:52.653
Cold? You look cold.

42:53.655 --> 42:56.240
I guess it has something
to do with the weather.

42:57.992 --> 42:59.701
Here, take my coat.

43:00.370 --> 43:03.789
No, thanks.
Where's your boyfriend?

43:04.332 --> 43:07.334
Him. Forget it. He ain't got no manners.

43:09.087 --> 43:11.421
I'm Jewel,
if you wanna know.

43:13.174 --> 43:15.259
I'm Robert.

43:15.343 --> 43:16.593
Hi.

43:17.887 --> 43:20.514
Well, I been living here
about six years now.

43:21.516 --> 43:23.725
It ain't Disneyland.

43:23.810 --> 43:25.352
You been to Disneyland?

43:25.436 --> 43:26.561
Sure.

43:26.688 --> 43:29.231
You make it sound
like everybody has.

43:29.607 --> 43:31.441
I know you can't tell
by the way I look,

43:31.526 --> 43:34.069
but I ain't like the
other kids around here.

43:35.071 --> 43:37.864
Why? I mean, what
makes you so different?

43:37.949 --> 43:38.991
I don't know.

43:39.075 --> 43:40.117
I guess it's
'cause I wanna get out.

43:40.201 --> 43:41.994
You know how it is.

43:43.788 --> 43:48.583
You know, for an Italian kid,
you ain't got a bad butt.

43:50.169 --> 43:51.712
Shut up, man.
Let's go. Come on.

43:57.635 --> 43:59.970
First money I get,
I'm going to Miami.

44:00.054 --> 44:01.305
Why Miami?

44:01.389 --> 44:03.223
Miami needs
new gigolos.

44:03.308 --> 44:05.475
Yeah, I read
something like that.

44:05.935 --> 44:07.102
Ow.

44:08.730 --> 44:10.230
My back is getting bad.

44:10.315 --> 44:12.274
How come you
don't have arthritis?

44:12.358 --> 44:13.483
Yo, ain't I got enough?

44:13.568 --> 44:15.235
Hey,
watch where you're going.

44:15.320 --> 44:17.112
Adrian's too good for this.

44:18.364 --> 44:20.657
This place is really depressing,
Paulie, you know? It's...

44:20.742 --> 44:21.742
Yo, Rock,
come inside.

44:21.826 --> 44:23.869
Everybody's been asking
for you. You too, Paulie.

44:23.953 --> 44:25.620
Hey, no, thanks.
I'm a little beat.

44:25.705 --> 44:27.247
I'm a little thirsty.

44:27.332 --> 44:28.498
Hey, you go if you want to, Paulie.

44:28.583 --> 44:29.541
Mr. Balboa?

44:29.625 --> 44:31.293
Look at this.
Tommy Gunn.

44:31.377 --> 44:32.961
Yo, why you still
hanging around, kid?

44:33.046 --> 44:35.005
Is there something
I can do for you?

44:35.089 --> 44:37.424
Yeah. I'd like
to try again.

44:38.051 --> 44:39.926
Hey, kid, you know,
I'd like to help you out,

44:40.011 --> 44:42.095
but I really don't know
nothing about no managing.

44:42.180 --> 44:43.680
All I'm asking
for is a chance.

44:43.765 --> 44:45.349
Man, if I screw up or do
something you don't like,

44:45.433 --> 44:47.142
man, you don't have to throw
me out. Hell, I'll leave.

44:47.226 --> 44:48.352
What have you
got to lose?

44:48.436 --> 44:50.228
Me? Nothing. I ain't
got nothing to lose.

44:50.313 --> 44:51.355
It's what you got to lose.

44:51.439 --> 44:52.814
And I got nothing to lose.

44:52.899 --> 44:54.024
Maybe you do. Like, look,

44:54.108 --> 44:55.484
what if I don't
do good, right?

44:55.568 --> 44:57.402
You know,
and you don't make it?

44:57.487 --> 45:00.655
I don't want you blaming me
for this, kid, you know?

45:00.740 --> 45:02.366
You know, here's what
I would do if I was you.

45:02.450 --> 45:03.450
No, listen to me.

45:03.534 --> 45:05.535
If I was you,
here's what I would do.

45:05.620 --> 45:08.288
I would go home, and I'd
talk to your family people.

45:08.373 --> 45:10.207
Maybe you could come up with
something better, you know?

45:10.291 --> 45:11.708
I got no family people.

45:11.793 --> 45:13.668
Man, all I got is
what you see here.

45:13.753 --> 45:14.920
Man, I know everything about you

45:15.004 --> 45:17.130
from back when you had your
first fight with Apollo Creed.

45:17.256 --> 45:18.882
Yeah. I read how nobody cared about you,

45:18.966 --> 45:20.509
how no one ever
gave you a chance.

45:20.593 --> 45:22.552
And I realize I don't come
from the same streets as you do,

45:22.637 --> 45:24.513
but I'm hungry
like you were.

45:24.597 --> 45:25.847
And ever since
I put on gloves,

45:25.932 --> 45:27.140
I've been
waiting to meet you,

45:27.225 --> 45:30.310
'cause I knew that if anybody
could make me a winner, it was you.

45:31.229 --> 45:34.564
Winner. Hey, Paulie, you
see a winner standing here?

45:34.649 --> 45:36.525
Yes! Man,
you beat the best!

45:36.609 --> 45:38.276
Nobody could ever
say any different.

45:38.361 --> 45:40.278
Look, Rock,
you don't know me,

45:40.363 --> 45:42.531
but anything you want me to do, I'll do.

45:42.615 --> 45:45.158
And if I can't,
I'll bust my butt trying.

45:45.243 --> 45:46.618
Man, I'm not
hustling you, man.

45:46.702 --> 45:48.703
All I'm asking
for is a chance.

45:48.788 --> 45:50.247
Man, just one shot.

46:01.092 --> 46:02.676
Are you hungry?

46:04.846 --> 46:06.221
Yeah.

46:06.305 --> 46:07.431
Yeah?

46:08.182 --> 46:09.391
Come on.

46:09.851 --> 46:12.394
You're really gonna like the
way Adrian cooks, you know.

46:12.478 --> 46:15.188
She does, like, amazing
things with macaroni,

46:15.273 --> 46:16.314
especially tomatoes.

46:16.399 --> 46:17.899
But I gotta warn you.

46:17.984 --> 46:20.026
She can be a little
vicious with the garlic.

46:22.697 --> 46:25.198
So, why'd this kid
smack your face for?

46:25.283 --> 46:26.741
It really doesn't matter, Dad. Sorry.

46:26.826 --> 46:27.826
Hell, sure, it matters.

46:27.910 --> 46:29.494
It does matter.
They took his coat.

46:29.579 --> 46:31.037
No. They... Look, I don't want the coat.

46:31.122 --> 46:32.414
They took the one
with the collar?

46:32.498 --> 46:34.124
I'm gonna go to your
school tomorrow and just...

46:34.208 --> 46:35.917
Yeah, you should. You'll only
make things worse if you go.

46:36.002 --> 46:37.085
Can't I do what
I think is right?

46:37.170 --> 46:38.795
Well, you know, what
do you think is right?

46:38.880 --> 46:40.672
A baseball bat across
the face would be nice.

46:40.756 --> 46:42.132
Paulie, what are
you telling this kid?

46:42.216 --> 46:43.341
Adrian, can I have
the plate?

46:43.426 --> 46:44.634
I'm sorry, yes, Rocky.

46:44.719 --> 46:46.970
You know, I had trouble one
time when I was in school.

46:47.054 --> 46:49.264
It seemed like every day
I got chased by this one kid,

46:49.348 --> 46:51.391
till one day my mother
said to me, she said,

46:51.476 --> 46:53.226
"Just pretend
the guy's like a balloon. "

46:53.311 --> 46:54.519
Balloon?

46:54.604 --> 46:57.481
She said if you pop him hard,
these guys just go away.

47:00.234 --> 47:02.652
Tommy, we're trying to raise our son

47:02.737 --> 47:05.197
so he can handle
his problems with his mind,

47:05.281 --> 47:06.573
not his muscles.

47:07.241 --> 47:08.241
Sorry.

47:08.326 --> 47:09.326
That's why I'm
gonna get mangled.

47:09.410 --> 47:11.328
No, you ain't gonna
get mangled.

47:11.412 --> 47:13.163
Dad, will you
teach me how to fight?

47:13.247 --> 47:14.915
A baseball bat
would be nice.

47:14.999 --> 47:17.918
Come on. Do you want to grow
up and just use your fists?

47:18.002 --> 47:20.378
You know, Adrian, I don't
think it would be so bad

47:20.463 --> 47:24.841
if I taught him how to throw
a few deadly punches, you know.

47:24.926 --> 47:26.843
Tommy, did your Dad
teach you how to fight?

47:27.220 --> 47:28.512
No. Not exactly.
I had to...

47:28.596 --> 47:29.638
What?

47:29.722 --> 47:30.805
Come on, sweetheart,
don't get personal.

47:30.890 --> 47:31.890
No, it's okay.

47:31.974 --> 47:35.143
See, my old man, he used
to drink a lot, seriously.

47:35.228 --> 47:37.521
He'd go out with his
friends and tie one on,

47:37.605 --> 47:39.189
then he'd come home
and look to punch on me.

47:39.273 --> 47:41.525
You know, he'd punch on my mother, too.

47:41.609 --> 47:43.276
He did that
a lot of times.

47:43.361 --> 47:45.695
You know, so, growing up, I never
really thought about fighting anybody

47:45.780 --> 47:46.988
but my father.

47:47.073 --> 47:50.116
You know, when I was 13,
I got in trouble at school.

47:50.201 --> 47:52.369
He tied me down
and he whipped me so bad

47:52.453 --> 47:53.745
I couldn't walk for a week.

47:53.829 --> 47:55.288
Just couldn't do anything.

47:56.499 --> 47:59.417
But, I tell you, the first guy
I ever knocked out was my father.

47:59.502 --> 48:03.046
And now when I get in the ring,
it's like all I see is him.

48:03.130 --> 48:05.257
That's kind of sick, huh?

48:06.092 --> 48:07.759
Hey, yo, Tommy.
At least you had

48:07.843 --> 48:09.636
an old man to
knock out, you know.

48:12.098 --> 48:13.265
Yeah.

48:14.600 --> 48:16.601
Some of us didn't even
have that, you know?

48:16.686 --> 48:18.436
Yeah, someday you could
punch out your pop.

48:18.521 --> 48:21.189
Hey, yo, Paulie, what are you
telling the kid things like this?

48:21.274 --> 48:23.149
Hey, it's fittest
of the survival.

48:24.569 --> 48:25.860
Hey, Tommy,

48:25.945 --> 48:27.696
where you staying tonight?
You got a place?

48:27.780 --> 48:30.323
I'll find someplace to stay.
I mean...

48:30.408 --> 48:32.701
No, I tell you, we got
room down in the basement.

48:32.785 --> 48:33.785
It's not...
It's nice, I don't know.

48:33.869 --> 48:34.869
What about me?

48:34.954 --> 48:37.163
Wait, now, sweetheart. Your
son is sleeping down there.

48:37.248 --> 48:39.958
No, well, he can stay
with his uncle, right?

48:40.042 --> 48:41.209
What the hell am I?
A pit stop?

48:41.335 --> 48:43.336
No... Hey, I don't want
to cause any problems.

48:43.421 --> 48:44.671
I mean, I can find someplace to stay.

48:44.755 --> 48:46.298
No, it's okay.
You know, it's just

48:46.382 --> 48:49.551
for a little while,
you know, right?

48:49.635 --> 48:51.261
No problem at all. You
know, it'll be all right.

48:51.345 --> 48:53.805
Hey, kid, I appreciate it. Is
that all right? It's cold outside.

48:53.889 --> 48:55.432
Hey, I'm not
changing no sheets.

48:55.516 --> 48:57.767
Hey, since when
have you ever?

48:58.769 --> 49:00.228
Hey, Tommy, why don't
you come on down

49:00.313 --> 49:02.731
and we'll show
you the whole place?

49:02.815 --> 49:04.024
Sweetheart, why don't you go downstairs,

49:04.108 --> 49:05.108
show your Father
what you did today?

49:05.192 --> 49:07.027
Come on. Come on.

49:11.657 --> 49:14.159
Hey, junior, your plumbing
don't leak, do it?

49:21.792 --> 49:22.834
You know this guy?

49:22.918 --> 49:24.502
Yeah. He hits hard.

49:27.381 --> 49:28.965
You know, Adrian, man,
she can really cook.

49:29.050 --> 49:30.133
Yeah,
she's okay.

49:30.217 --> 49:31.760
Listen, Tommy,
we ain't had a chance

49:31.844 --> 49:34.638
to get this place
too nice, so...

49:34.722 --> 49:37.098
I'll get it together in
a little while, you know.

49:38.142 --> 49:40.602
Wow, man! This is what it's all about!

49:40.686 --> 49:41.936
Holy mackerel...
Well, I...

49:42.021 --> 49:44.230
Why do you keep
this stuff down here?

49:44.315 --> 49:45.649
When did you get
a chance to do this?

49:45.733 --> 49:46.900
He took
everything out of a box

49:46.984 --> 49:48.485
and fixed this up like this.
It's beautiful!

49:48.569 --> 49:52.197
And you painted! When'd you
get a chance to do this, kid?

49:52.281 --> 49:54.157
After school.
It's no big deal.

49:54.241 --> 49:56.159
If you don't mind me asking,
where'd you get the glove?

49:56.243 --> 49:57.243
This?
Yeah.

49:57.328 --> 49:59.287
Thanks. This is one
of my favorite objects.

49:59.372 --> 50:02.207
You know, like, Mickey give
me this before he departed.

50:02.291 --> 50:04.793
It was Rocky Marciano's
cufflink that we had fixed.

50:04.877 --> 50:06.961
Really? The real Rocky Marciano? Yeah.

50:07.046 --> 50:08.797
Yeah. You know, you got me
thinking about Mick.

50:08.881 --> 50:10.382
I wanna show you something.
Come on.

50:10.466 --> 50:14.094
He told me a long time ago.
He says that,

50:15.221 --> 50:17.889
fightin' is like,
90% in the skull

50:17.973 --> 50:19.265
and 10% in the body.

50:19.350 --> 50:20.558
This is what
he says to me.

50:20.643 --> 50:23.561
Hey, Dad, I met this really
nice girl today. She's great.

50:23.646 --> 50:24.729
Yeah? Really?
That's wonderful.

50:24.814 --> 50:27.065
Yeah, she's a lot
better than Sarah.

50:27.149 --> 50:28.608
Hey,
don't change the station.

50:28.693 --> 50:30.068
I'll be right back with you.

50:30.152 --> 50:32.946
I just wanna tell Tommy
a few things, you know? Hey.

50:33.030 --> 50:35.949
Who was your best
friend back in Orlando?

50:36.033 --> 50:38.243
That's...
That's Oklahoma.

50:38.327 --> 50:40.286
Right, well, yeah.
Eric Elder.

50:40.371 --> 50:44.499
No, no, no. No, your best friend
is a guy named Frankie Fear.

50:44.583 --> 50:47.252
You see, fear is
a fighter's best friend.

50:47.336 --> 50:49.295
You know, but it ain't
nothing to be ashamed of.

50:49.380 --> 50:52.298
See, fear keeps you sharp,
it keeps you awake,

50:52.383 --> 50:54.426
you know, it makes you want to
survive. You know what I mean?

50:54.510 --> 50:57.887
But the thing is, you gotta learn
how to control it. All right?

50:57.972 --> 50:59.889
'Cause fear is like
this fire, all right?

50:59.974 --> 51:01.766
And it's burning deep inside.

51:01.851 --> 51:05.186
Now, if you control it,
Tommy, it's gonna make you hot.

51:05.271 --> 51:07.772
But, you see, if this
thing here, it controls you,

51:07.857 --> 51:10.734
it's gonna burn you and
everything else around you up.

51:10.818 --> 51:12.110
That's right, you know?

51:12.194 --> 51:15.697
Anyway, these are the
things that was taught to me,

51:15.781 --> 51:18.658
and if you want,
I'd like to teach to you.

51:19.201 --> 51:21.953
So, this... This mean
you're gonna manage me?

51:22.037 --> 51:24.038
Absolutely.
Hey, home team! Okay!

51:24.123 --> 51:25.373
All right! Yeah!

51:25.458 --> 51:26.750
Let's go for it.
Hey, Rock,

51:26.834 --> 51:28.918
as long as we're down here, do
you mind showing me a few things?

51:29.003 --> 51:31.337
Sure, Tommy. I'm gonna
show you a lot of things.

51:36.594 --> 51:39.637
Hey, rich boy, how much you
got in your pocket today?

51:39.722 --> 51:41.473
Nothing.
Come on, let's have it.

51:41.557 --> 51:42.932
Nothing. I got nothing.

51:43.017 --> 51:44.476
Come on. Give me the money.

51:44.560 --> 51:45.894
Come on!

51:45.978 --> 51:47.228
Hey, I gotta eat.

51:47.313 --> 51:50.440
He's hungry. He's gotta
eat. Well, eat this!

51:53.360 --> 51:54.736
I got it. I got it. Go.

51:55.696 --> 51:58.698
Father Carmine! Yo!

51:59.200 --> 52:01.034
Father Carmine!

52:01.118 --> 52:02.118
You know,
maybe he's not home.

52:02.203 --> 52:03.787
No, priests is always home.

52:03.871 --> 52:05.246
Rocky!

52:05.331 --> 52:06.456
Yo!

52:08.667 --> 52:11.461
Well, I didn't want to
disturb you that much, Father.

52:14.048 --> 52:15.089
Excellent.

52:15.174 --> 52:17.091
Everything is perfect.
You know...

52:17.176 --> 52:19.469
Father, this is my
new friend, Tommy Gunn.

52:24.475 --> 52:26.851
Well, I was wondering... You
know, Tommy here is a fighter,

52:26.936 --> 52:28.686
and I'm supposed to be
his manager, you know?

52:28.771 --> 52:30.522
So I was wondering if
you could do me a favor,

52:30.606 --> 52:31.815
you know,
if you ain't that busy.

52:31.899 --> 52:34.234
If you could throw us down
a couple blessings, you know?

52:34.318 --> 52:36.861
One, that I don't
mess up being a manager,

52:36.946 --> 52:39.656
and B, that Tommy does as
good as I think he can do.

52:39.740 --> 52:42.992
You know, great, and don't get
hurt none. Could you do that?

52:51.252 --> 52:52.418
I love when he does that.

52:52.503 --> 52:55.004
Hey, thanks, Father.
I really appreciate this.

52:56.215 --> 52:57.215
Anytime.

52:57.299 --> 52:59.092
Okay. Hey, I'll see you
in church!

53:01.679 --> 53:02.679
Okay.

53:02.763 --> 53:03.930
Hey, man, what'd you do this for?

53:04.014 --> 53:06.474
Hey, it don't hurt having an
angel in your corner, you know?

53:06.642 --> 53:07.684
Come on!

53:11.814 --> 53:13.523
Hey, Rock,
how's it going?

53:13.607 --> 53:14.732
Doing great, guys!

53:14.817 --> 53:16.609
Better slow down, we're
gonna give you a ticket.

53:16.694 --> 53:18.528
This is Tommy Gunn.
He's gonna be champ, guys.

53:18.612 --> 53:19.779
How you doing, Tom?

53:30.291 --> 53:33.084
Break it up. Break! Break! Break it!

53:45.431 --> 53:46.598
Get off the ropes.

53:54.607 --> 53:55.648
Just go easy, all right?

53:55.733 --> 53:56.733
Man, I need more work.

53:56.817 --> 53:58.401
No, no, no, you're ready.
No, I need more work.

53:58.485 --> 53:59.611
This guy's killing me.

53:59.653 --> 54:01.362
Now, listen to me. You're
ready now. He's killing me.

54:01.447 --> 54:02.947
No, you're perfect,
you understanding me?

54:02.990 --> 54:04.741
Man, I feel weak. I feel
weak. No, no, no. Listen to me.

54:04.825 --> 54:05.867
Shut up! Listen to me.

54:05.951 --> 54:07.785
Mick used to say
the only difference

54:07.870 --> 54:10.914
between a hero and a coward is
the hero's willing to go for it.

54:10.998 --> 54:12.582
All right? He's willing
to take the shot, okay?

54:12.666 --> 54:14.042
Now, this guy over
here is scared, too.

54:14.126 --> 54:15.835
You're scared. He's
scared. You're both scared.

54:15.920 --> 54:18.087
Remember, in the basement,
when we was talking about fear

54:18.172 --> 54:19.797
and how it's
like this fire, huh?

54:19.882 --> 54:22.383
And you gotta control it 'cause
it's like, it'll, like, burn you up

54:22.468 --> 54:23.760
or it's gonna burn him up.
All right?

54:23.844 --> 54:25.845
Now, you gotta make it
work for you, Tommy, okay?

54:25.930 --> 54:27.722
I would never do nothing
that would hurt you.

54:27.806 --> 54:29.015
You gotta understand
what I'm saying.

54:29.099 --> 54:30.558
Now, fear is like
this fire, okay?

54:30.643 --> 54:33.686
Now, let it burn and burn until
it becomes like this volcano,

54:33.771 --> 54:35.772
and when the time is right,
and you see the opening,

54:35.856 --> 54:37.440
explode all over
this guy, okay?

54:37.524 --> 54:38.858
Now, you can take him, okay?

54:38.901 --> 54:40.360
It's all heart, you
understand? Okay. Got it.

54:40.444 --> 54:42.612
It ain't all muscle, it's
all heart. Heart and fire.

54:42.696 --> 54:43.947
Heart and fire! Okay.

54:44.031 --> 54:44.989
Now you do it.

54:47.701 --> 54:50.370
Remember, I'm like this angel
sitting on your shoulder, okay?

54:50.454 --> 54:52.205
I ain't gonna let nothing
happen to you, okay?

54:52.289 --> 54:53.289
Go!
Got it.

54:54.625 --> 54:55.917
Go for it

54:57.836 --> 54:59.545
Come on, Tommy, jab!

55:03.300 --> 55:05.802
Explode! Left, right!

55:08.472 --> 55:09.597
The body! The body!

55:10.724 --> 55:11.766
Hook!

55:13.394 --> 55:14.352
All right!

55:14.436 --> 55:16.354
Are you gonna stop
or keep on rushin'

55:16.438 --> 55:18.648
Farther, faster,
quicker than the next man

55:18.732 --> 55:20.608
To be the best
is the master plan

55:20.693 --> 55:22.902
Go on with all you got
Give it your best shot

55:22.987 --> 55:24.737
Don't ever think
about trying to stop

55:24.822 --> 55:27.323
Keep reaching, pushing
hoping for perfection

55:27.408 --> 55:29.033
Make up the direction

55:29.118 --> 55:31.035
Don't ever stop for a moment

55:31.120 --> 55:32.662
If you got it, flaunt it

55:32.746 --> 55:33.830
And get up on it

55:33.914 --> 55:36.249
Go for yours not for a
minute but all the time

55:36.333 --> 55:38.084
You better do it
'cause I'm going for mine

55:40.254 --> 55:41.337
Yeah!

55:41.422 --> 55:42.588
Go for it

55:42.673 --> 55:44.549
Go, go, go

55:44.633 --> 55:47.093
I see it in your eyes

55:47.177 --> 55:48.553
Time!

55:52.725 --> 55:55.518
You've got to go
for the feelin'

55:55.602 --> 55:57.687
It's time for the rhyme
of the bold and the gifted

55:57.771 --> 56:00.023
Listen closely
and you'll get lifted

56:00.107 --> 56:01.858
Like you've never
been before

56:01.942 --> 56:04.318
Get more than
you bargained for, for sure

56:04.403 --> 56:06.487
Life can be a trip
full of trouble

56:06.572 --> 56:08.698
But you gotta stand up
and fight back double

56:08.782 --> 56:10.825
Don't let nothin'
hold you back, yo

56:10.909 --> 56:13.661
When life says stop
you say go, go

56:13.746 --> 56:15.788
Go to the body, Tommy.
Come on.

56:15.873 --> 56:17.457
That's it,
that's it!

56:18.542 --> 56:21.127
Sam, you okay?
Hey, Tommy Gunn.

56:21.253 --> 56:23.796
You got some guns,
don't you? Paulie!

56:23.881 --> 56:25.631
'Cause I know
you got the knack

56:25.716 --> 56:27.550
To go farther than
you've ever been before

